🍉️1.To install postgress run the below comand.
   --> sudo apt-get install postgresql postgresql-contrib

🍉️2.To check postgres installed or not 
   --> ls etc/postgresql/11/main/   (11 is version number)

🍉️3.To check postgres running properly.
   --> service postgresql   (☘️It will show like this:Usage: /etc/init.d/postgresql {start|stop|restart|reload|force-reload|status} [version ..])

🍉️4.To know the status run the following comand.
   --> srvice postgresql status

🍉️5.To change the system previlage of sudo user to postgres account user.
   --> sudo su postgres

🍉️6.To enter postgres shell
   --> psql

🍉️7.To list the database.
   --> \l

🍉️8.To know the users.
  -->\du

🍉️9.To change the user password run the following comand.
   --> ALTER USER postgres WITH PASSWORD 'test1234'; (☘️It shows : ALTER ROLE)

🍉️9.To create the new user.
   --> CREATE USER user_2 WITH PASSWORD 'test1234';  (☘️It shows : CREATE ROLE)

🍉️11.To alter the previlage.
   --> ALTER USER user_2 WITH CREATEROLE;  (☘️ It shows : ALTER ROLE)

🍉️12.Deleting the User.
   --> DROP USER user_2;  (☘️ It shows : DROP ROLE)

🍉️13.To Open postgres documentation for help.
   --> man psql


